[normal]&#xa0;[bold]2.1
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]The Leprosy Mission, established in 1874, is an international development org
[normal]anisation working in 11 leprosy-
[normal]endemic countries to defeat leprosy and transform the lives of people affected by the disease.  It uses a holistic approach 
[normal]to development that addresses not only the medical aspects of leprosy and disability but promotes so
[normal]cial inclusion of those who have been stigmatised and disabled, supporting them to realise their human rights and live in dignity.
